import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of delay time?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Delay Time")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=['Average Distance'], y=[average_distance], palette='viridis')
    ax.axhline(average_distance, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {average_distance:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['origin_destination'] = data['origin'] + '-' + data['destination']
    origin_destination_counts = data['origin_destination'].value_counts().reset_index()
    origin_destination_counts.columns = ['origin_destination', 'count']
    origin_destination_counts['origin'] = origin_destination_counts['origin_destination'].apply(lambda x: x.split('-')[0])
    origin_destination_counts['destination'] = origin_destination_counts['origin_destination'].apply(lambda x: x.split('-')[1])

    pivot_table = origin_destination_counts.pivot_table(index='origin', columns='destination', values='count', fill_value=0)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.heatmap(pivot_table, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt='d', linewidths=.5)
    plt.title('Which origin and destination pairs are the most common?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Origin')
    plt.legend(title='Counts', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
